messages.message:
Hi, Do we support these filetypes?
• Different variations of email such as .pst and .mbox
• GSlides and the Gsuite of Word, Excel, Powerpoint? We were asked this specifically as we currently are able to mount google drives in

Oh right! I missed that thank you; could we also update the docs?
https://aihub.instabase.com/docs/aihub/policies/limitations/index.html
@fernando.piazza.ctr cc regarding GNP - looks like gsheets, gdocs and gdocs are provided, can open a separate ticket for the other email file types he needs
@jean seems like we’re missing some of the supported files in the docs :point_up_2:
Also, this info might be better somewhere else. I don’t class those supported doc types as ‘limitations’ and wouldn’t expect to look there when trying to find out what is supported

Thank you, @Gwen, @Lee. So I understand we can tell GNP we support G-suite documents: G-Docs, G-Sheets, G-Slides. We'll need to show them how to do that next week. Gwen I'll organize the list of questions they sent us, so we can answer them point by point. Thanks a lot!

For sure, we can update the list, and I think there are some more formats coming in the next release as well. Additions to the list will be really important for eng to ticket/release note so that we can keep the docs updated.
I’ll come back on Monday to the nav issue around these, @Lee. I agree with you, I wouldn’t think to look for them there either.
